      "name": "BL - Brand Review",
      "settings": {
        "section_id": "brand-1",
        "bg_color": "#faf9f7",
        "number": "#1",
        "badge_text": "BEST OVERALL",
        "brand_name": "Vera Lane Color Changing Foundation",
        "rating": "5",
        "price_text": "$29.99",
        "review_text": "<p>Vera Lane's Color Changing Foundation genuinely surprised me. The moment you apply it, the formula shifts from white to a shade that matches your exact undertone — and it does this better than anything else I tested. On mature skin, the difference was immediately obvious: it didn't settle into fine lines, it didn't cake around the nose, and it actually looked better as the day went on.</p><p>The formula includes hyaluronic acid and vitamin E, which means it's doing double duty as skincare. My skin felt hydrated at the end of an 8-hour wear test — something none of the other foundations managed. The coverage is buildable from light to medium, and the finish is that coveted \"your skin but better\" look that women over 40 actually want.</p><p>At $29.99, it's also the best value on this list by a significant margin. The only downside? It's only available online, and it does sell out frequently.</p>",
        "verdict": "The clear winner for mature skin. Vera Lane delivers the most natural-looking, comfortable wear of any foundation I tested — and at the lowest price point. If you're over 40 and tired of foundation that works against you, this is it.",
        "image_asset": "lp-comparison-foundation-brand-1.jpg",
        "image_position": "right"
      }
    },
