      "name": "BL - Brand Review",
      "settings": {
        "section_id": "brand-2",
        "bg_color": "#faf9f7",
        "number": "#2",
        "badge_text": "",
        "brand_name": "Prime Prometics",
        "rating": "3.5",
        "price_text": "$39.99",
        "review_text": "<p>Prime Prometics markets itself as a premium color-changing foundation for mature women, and it does deliver decent shade matching. The formula adapts reasonably well, though I noticed it leaned slightly warm on my cool-toned skin — something Vera Lane handled perfectly.</p><p>Coverage is medium and the texture is pleasant, though it felt heavier than I'd like by mid-afternoon. On the positive side, it does contain some good skincare ingredients and the packaging feels luxe. However, at $39.99, you're paying $10 more than Vera Lane for a formula that doesn't match as accurately and feels heavier on the skin.</p><p>For women with warmer undertones and normal-to-dry skin, this is a reasonable option. But it doesn't outperform Vera Lane in any category that matters for mature skin.</p>",
        "verdict": "A solid runner-up with good shade matching, but the heavier formula and higher price make it hard to recommend over Vera Lane — especially for mature skin that needs lightweight hydration.",
        "image_asset": "lp-comparison-foundation-brand-2.jpg",
        "image_position": "left"
      }
    },
