      "name": "BL - Brand Review",
      "settings": {
        "section_id": "brand-4",
        "bg_color": "#faf9f7",
        "number": "#4",
        "badge_text": "",
        "brand_name": "Forever Bloom",
        "rating": "2.5",
        "price_text": "$27.99",
        "review_text": "<p>Forever Bloom is the budget option in this roundup, and unfortunately, you get what you pay for. The color-changing effect is minimal — it shifts slightly but never quite finds the right match. On my mature skin, it immediately settled into every fine line around my eyes and mouth, creating that crepe-paper effect we all dread.</p><p>The biggest problem is oxidation. Within two hours, the shade had turned noticeably orange — a common issue with cheaper color-adapting formulas that rely on pH rather than advanced skin-tone technology. By the afternoon, I'd wiped it off entirely.</p><p>The packaging is nice for the price, but that's about the only positive. For mature skin, this formula is too drying, too unstable, and too likely to oxidize into an unflattering shade.</p>",
        "verdict": "The lowest price on this list, but also the lowest performance. The severe oxidation and line-settling make it unsuitable for mature skin. Save the $27.99 and put it toward Vera Lane instead.",
        "image_asset": "lp-comparison-foundation-brand-4.jpg",
        "image_position": "left"
      }
    },
