      "name": "BL - Brand Review",
      "settings": {
        "section_id": "brand-5",
        "bg_color": "#faf9f7",
        "number": "#5",
        "badge_text": "",
        "brand_name": "Luxe",
        "rating": "3",
        "price_text": "$44.99",
        "review_text": "<p>Luxe positions itself as the premium choice in color-changing foundations, and the $44.99 price tag reflects that ambition. The formula does provide good coverage and a reasonably smooth application. However, the color-changing effect is subtle to the point of being questionable — it barely shifted on my skin, functioning more like a traditional medium-coverage foundation.</p><p>For mature skin, the formula is a mixed bag. Coverage is good and it handled age spots better than Meroda or Forever Bloom. But the texture is thick and sits on top of the skin rather than melting in, which can look heavy and aging on mature complexions. It also felt tight and drying by hour six.</p><p>At nearly $45, it's the most expensive option and doesn't deliver the tone-adapting benefits you'd expect from a color-changing foundation. You're essentially paying luxury prices for a decent — but ordinary — foundation.</p>",
        "verdict": "Premium price without premium color-changing performance. It's a decent traditional foundation, but if you're paying for tone-adapting technology, Vera Lane delivers far more at a fraction of the cost.",
        "image_asset": "lp-comparison-foundation-brand-5.jpg",
        "image_position": "right"
      }
    },
